{"id": 46, "ts": 1777959721.650692, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_4", "message": "I still see Eve as the strongest fit. Her recent leadership of a reliability\u2011critical program\u2014including handling outages and passing compliance audits\u2014directly aligns with the role\u2019s core focus on reliability, and she can start within two weeks with no conflicts. While Alice has impressive large\u2011scale leadership and a notable early delivery, the fact that her last organization missed multiple milestones after scaling beyond 80 engineers raises concerns about handling growth reliably. Carol\u2019s technical depth is valuable but her dismissiveness toward key partners poses coordination risks, and Bob\u2019s conflict and Dave\u2019s limited budget/headcount experience remain liabilities. Therefore, I continue to support Eve.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_4\", \"vote\": \"Eve\"}"}
